Example
Return the hostname of the current URL:

Copy
let x = location.hostname;

Description
The hostname property gets and sets the hostname of a URL.

Browser Compatibility
Chrome.png	Node.png	Firefox.png	Safari.png	Edge.png	Opera.png
hostname	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes	Yes
Syntax
Return the hostname property:

Copy
let a = location.hostname;
Set the hostname property:

Copy
location.hostname = hostname;
Property Values
Value	Type	Description
hostname	String	Specifies the hostname of the URL
Return Value
A String, representing the domain name, or the IP address of a URL.
